Codex loves safely checks. What if the user calls the voxel renderer with negative view distance? Then we discard all pixels at the beginning of the shader!

float maxDistance = voxelParams.params.x;
if (maxDistance <= 0.0) discard;

@algekalipso asked for more consciousness blogging.

Here's my attempt: an (almost) no-jargon primer on the hard problem, qualia, and the main theories. It is written for people like me who felt lost in all the terminology.

